cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.AR, cs.SY, cs.OS 

This paper is primarily focused on improving the performance of key-value stores, which is a topic that falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the use of near-data processing (NDP) to improve compaction, which is a topic that falls under the categories of computer architecture (cs.AR) and operating systems (cs.OS). Finally, the paper proposes a new approach to optimizing key-value stores, which could be considered a systems-level contribution and thus falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
